xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>563</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">sga1-i.8.3</fr:addr><fr:route>sga1-i.8.3.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>I.8.3</fr:number><fr:parent>sga1-i.8</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>The functor described in <fr:ref
addr="sga1-i.5.5"
href="sga1-i.5.5.xml"
taxon="Theorem"
number="I.5.5" /> is an <fr:em>equivalence</fr:em> of <fr:em>categories</fr:em>.</fr:p>
  
    
    <fr:tree
toc="false"
numbered="false"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>514</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="machine">#244</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-244.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:parent>sga1-i.8.3</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
    By <fr:ref
addr="sga1-i.5.5"
href="sga1-i.5.5.xml"
taxon="Theorem"
number="I.5.5" />, it remains only to show that every étale <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S_0]]></fr:tex>-scheme <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X_0]]></fr:tex> is isomorphic to an <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S_0]]></fr:tex>-scheme <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X\times _S S_0]]></fr:tex>, where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is an étale <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>-scheme.
    The underlying topological space of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> must necessarily be identical to the one of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X_0]]></fr:tex>, and with <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X_0]]></fr:tex> being identified with a closed sub-prescheme of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>.
    The problem is thus equivalent to the following:
    find, on the underlying topological space <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[|X_0|]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X_0]]></fr:tex>, a sheaf of algebras <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_X]]></fr:tex> over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_0^*(\mathcal {O}_S)]]></fr:tex> (where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_0]]></fr:tex> is the projection <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X_0\to  S_0]]></fr:tex>, thought of here as a continuous map of the underlying spaces) that makes <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[|X_0|]]></fr:tex> an étale <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>-prescheme <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>, as well as an algebra homomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_X\to \mathcal {O}_{X_0}]]></fr:tex> that is compatible with the homomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_0^*(\mathcal {O}_S)\to  f_0^*(\mathcal {O}_{S_0})]]></fr:tex> on the sheaves of scalars, and that induces an isomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_X\otimes _{f_0^*(\mathcal {O}_S)*}f_0^*(\mathcal {O}_{S_0})\xrightarrow {\sim }\mathcal {O}_{X_0}]]></fr:tex>.
    (Then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> will be an étale <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>-prescheme that is reduced along <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X_0]]></fr:tex>, and thus separated over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>, since <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X_0]]></fr:tex> is separated over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S_0]]></fr:tex>, and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> satisfies all the desired properties).

    If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(U_i)]]></fr:tex> is an open cover of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X_0]]></fr:tex>, and if we find a solution to the problem on each of the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U_i]]></fr:tex>, then it follows from the uniqueness theorem <fr:ref
addr="sga1-i.5.5"
href="sga1-i.5.5.xml"
taxon="Theorem"
number="I.5.5" /> that these solutions glue (i.e. the sheaves of algebras that they define, endowed with their augmentation homomorphisms, glue), and we claim that the ringed space thus constructed over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> is an étale <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>-prescheme <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> endowed with an isomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X\times _S S_0\xleftarrow {\sim }X_0]]></fr:tex>.
    It thus suffices to find a solution locally, which we know is possible by <fr:ref
addr="sga1-i.8.1"
href="sga1-i.8.1.xml"
taxon="Proposition"
number="I.8.1" />.
  </fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
  
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
