display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> be the rank of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[L=B\otimes _A K(A)]]></fr:tex> over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[K(A)=k]]></fr:tex>.
    For <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> to be unramified (resp. étale) over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, it is necessary and sufficient that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> be isomorphic to a quotient of (resp. isomorphic to) <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A[t]/FA[t]]]></fr:tex>, where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> is a separable monic polynomial, which we can assume to be (resp. which is necessarily of) degree <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
  
    
    <fr:tree
