xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>457</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="machine">#250</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-250.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:parent>sga1-i.7.5</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>We only have to prove necessity.
      Suppose that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> is unramified over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, and thus that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> is separable over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[k]]></fr:tex>.
      It then follows from the hypotheses that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[L/k]]></fr:tex> admits a generator <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\xi ]]></fr:tex>, and so the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\xi ^i]]></fr:tex> (for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[0\leq  i<n]]></fr:tex>) form a basis for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[k]]></fr:tex>.
      Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[u\in  B]]></fr:tex> be a lift of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\xi ]]></fr:tex>;
      by Nakayama, the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[u^i]]></fr:tex> (for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[0\leq  i<n]]></fr:tex>) generate (resp. form a basis of) the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>-module <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>, and, in particular, we obtain a monic polynomial <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F\in  A[t]]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F(u)=0]]></fr:tex>;
      then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> is isomorphic to a quotient of (resp. isomorphic to) <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A[t]/FA[t]]]></fr:tex>.
      Finally, by applying <fr:ref
addr="sga1-i.7.4"
href="sga1-i.7.4.xml"
taxon="Corollary"
number="I.7.4" /> to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[L/k]]></fr:tex>, we see that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F']]></fr:tex> generate <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A[t]]]></fr:tex> modulo <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {m}A[t]]]></fr:tex>, and so (by Nakayama in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A[t]/FA[t]]]></fr:tex>) <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F']]></fr:tex> generate <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A[t]]]></fr:tex>, and we are done.</fr:p>
